main_body:
The following Member States are authorised to import, under the quotas referred to in Article 1 and on the terms laid down in Article 2(1), the following shortfall expressed as white sugar:
(a) Finland: 44000 tonnes;
(b) metropolitan France: 3000 tonnes;
(c) mainland Portugal: 158000 tonnes;
(d) United Kingdom: 5000 tonnes.
